        "collapsible_tab_Ta8cMT": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Made in Italy",
            "icon": "none",
            "content": "<p>Our <strong>Breton Shirts</strong> are crafted just a few kilometers from <strong>Venice</strong>, in a region known for its rich artisanal heritage and its role in producing garments for the world’s top <strong>high-fashion brands</strong>.</p><p>Each piece is meticulously made from <strong>fine merino wool</strong>, prized for its natural <strong>softness</strong> and <strong>thermo-regulating properties</strong>, ensuring comfort in any season.</p><p>We collaborate with a <strong>small, family-run workshop</strong>, fostering a partnership built on <strong>trust, craftsmanship, and a passion for quality</strong>—values that define every garment we create.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_9wCejz": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Merino Wool from Italy",
            "icon": "none",
            "content": "<p>We have chosen one of the best manufacturers in the world of merino wool: <strong>Tollegno 1900</strong>. It is a historic Italian company specializing in the production of the highest quality wools. Located in the town of Tollegno, in the province of Biella, at the foot of the Piedmont Alps, Tollegno 1900 operates ethically and holds the most important eco-certifications in the textile industry, making it a <strong>green and sustainable company.</strong></p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_T6nwD3": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Handmade Embroidery",
            "icon": "none",
            "content": "<p>Our Marinières are hand embroidered with needle and thread, making each one unique. </p><p>Each pieces is also hand numbered, from 1 to 99.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
